Leidos is seeking a motivated intern to support our work in Human Factors research. The position will be based out of our Arlington, VA office OR San Diego, CA. However, this position is available as remote work or onsite.This candidate will work with other researchers and engineers in research projects focused on developing innovative data science solutions. Tasks involved in this research include adapting and extending data science technologies to new applications, developing prototypes, drafting research papers, and supporting existing human factors programs. The candidate must be intellectually adaptive, inquisitive, communicative, a self-starter and problem-solver, and self-managed when necessary. The intern will be responsible for developing, defending, executing and presenting the results of a research plan.Primary Responsibilities-At the direction of the project lead, analyze and assess internal projects and artifacts as part of developing innovative data science solutions.- Support analysis and interpretation of experimental results by senior researchers and decision-makers.- Communicate plans and results effectively through written status reports and presentations.Basic Qualifications- Pursuing a Degree in Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, Mathematics, or a related technical field.- Has experience with programming languages such as Java, Scala, C/C++, Ruby, Rust, or Python.- Coursework in human factors.- Ability to obtain and maintain a DoD security clearance.- US citizenship required.Preferred Qualifications- Hands-on experience working with human factors theories and technologies- Demonstrable experience and curiosity in human factors.If you're looking for comfort, keep scrolling. At Leidos, we outthink, outbuild, and outpace the status quo — because the mission demands it. We're not hiring followers. We're recruiting the ones who disrupt, provoke, and refuse to fail. We're already at step 30 — and moving faster than anyone else dares.Original Posting:November 10, 2025For U.S. Positions: While subject to change based on business needs, Leidos reasonably anticipates that this job requisition will remain open for at least 3 days with an anticipated close date of no earlier than 3 days after the original posting date as listed above.Pay Range:Pay Range $48,100.00 - $86,950.00The Leidos pay range for this job level is a general guideline only and not a guarantee of compensation or salary. Additional factors considered in extending an offer include (but are not limited to) responsibilities of the job, education, experience, knowledge, skills, and abilities, as well as internal equity, alignment with market data, applicable bargaining agreement (if any), or other law.

Nice to meet you!  

We’re the leader in data and AI. Through our software and services, we inspire customers around the world to transform data into intelligence – and questions into answers.  

 

If you’re looking for a dynamic, fulfilling career with flexibility and a world-class employee experience, you’ll find it here. We’re recognized around the world for our inclusive, meaningful culture and innovative technologies by organizations like Fast Company, Forbes, Newsweek and more.    

  

What you’ll do 

Looking for *that* internship? The game-changing one that’ll help you learn, grow, and chart your path forward? You’ll find it at SAS. Our interns aren’t coffee runners – they do real, meaningful work. Our award-winning internship program is focused on development, culture, and community. We’ll help you grow professionally, find (or further) your passion, and make memorable connections that last beyond the summer.  

 

The IoT Division at SAS is a vertically integrated line of business charged with innovation: innovation in products and solutions and innovation around market engagement.   

 

We are looking for a curious and innovative candidate who believes that AI can make a real difference for IoT applications. Within our Strategy and Product Innovation & Engineering team, we are developing a brand-new paradigm in delivering AI and IoT applications.   

 

As an intern, you might:  

  • Research and Conduct proof of concept focused on AI capabilities including language models, embedding models, Agentic frameworks, RAG and NLP techniques.  
  • Develop Application prototypes for new feature ideas  
  • Support packaging and deployment of AI and IoT applications  
  • Collaborate with R&D, Product Management, and Industry advisory teams  

 

Required Qualifications  

  • You are a Graduate student studying Computer Science or a related field, not graduating prior to December 2026.  
  • Strong Python experience with knowledge of multithreading and object-oriented programming. 
  • Good knowledge of Generative AI technologies such as language models, embedding models, Agentic frameworks and NLP techniques.  
  • Familiarity with Application development technologies such React, GoLang, APIs.  
  • Familiarity with containers and container orchestration technologies such as Docker and Kubernetes. 

 

Preferred Qualifications  

 

  • Familiarity with cloud Infrastructure (Azure, AWS, or GCP) 
  • Understanding of model inferencing and optimization techniques 
  • DevOps understanding   

 

Timeline 

  • Applications open: October 31, 2025
  • Applications close: This application will close early to mid-November 2025
  • Interviews begin:  November 2025
  • Internship: May 19, 2026 – August 7, 2026.

  

Perks of the job 

  • Work with (and learn from) the best. As a SAS intern, you’ll get face time with our top executives! 
  • Free SAS programming training and certification.   
  • At SAS, flexible work is the norm. Want to work remotely? That’s cool. Prefer a hybrid mix of sweatpants and in-person collaboration? That’s great, too.  
  • We work hard, but we like to play hard, too. Enjoy hackathons, social events and other opportunities to connect + engage.  
  • Your well-being matters, and that’s why we support all dimensions of your well-being by offering programs that reduce stress and distractions to help you stay healthy and productive.  This includes an on-site and remote Work/Life Center staffed by master’s level social workers and an Employee Assistance Program.

 

Diverse and inclusive  

At SAS, it’s not about fitting into our culture – it’s about adding to it. We believe our people make the difference. Our diverse workforce brings together unique talents and inspires teams to create amazing software that reflects the diversity of our users and customers. Our commitment to diversity is a priority to our leadership, all the way up to the top; and it’s essential to who we are. To put it plainly: you are welcome here.    

  

Additional Information

To qualify, applicants must be legally authorized to work in the United States, and should not require, now or in the future, sponsorship for employment visa status. SAS is an equal opportunity/Affirmative Action employer. All qualified applicants are considered for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status or any other characteristic protected by law. Read more: Know Your Rights. Also view the Pay Transparency notice.

 

Resumes may be considered in the order they are received. SAS employees performing certain job functions may require access to technology or software subject to export or import regulations. To comply with these regulations, SAS may obtain nationality or citizenship information from applicants for employment. SAS collects this information solely for trade law compliance purposes and does not use it to discriminate unfairly in the hiring process.

 

SAS only sends emails from verified “sas.com” email addresses and never asks for sensitive, personal information or money. If you have any doubts about the authenticity of any type of communication from, or on behalf of SAS, please contact Recruitingsupport@sas.com.

 

Pay Transparency: The hourly rate for SAS internships is determined by the applicant’s year in school and the position they are hired into. job_description:
Overview

The education policy team’s data intern will support the team’s cutting-edge research at the intersection of data, education policy, and technology. The data intern will research a variety of topics, including by:• analyzing and drawing meaningful interpretations from state and national education data sets;• using statistical modeling to estimate causal effects;• using web scraping to construct novel education data sets;• applying text analysis, machine learning, and other techniques to analyze unstructured data; and• creating visualizations and written reports to communicate results.

Candidates are expected to:• be highly interested in learning more about education policy;• have keen attention to detail and be highly effective at communication;• be highly proficient in Python and/or R.• have a strong understanding of statistics;• have a foundational understanding of machine learning;• be comfortable working independently when given a project; and• be able and eager to learn new skills on the job.

 

Applicants who go above and beyond will:• have taken coursework to understand, or have work experience in, education policy; and• demonstrate fluency in both Python and R, and potentially other programming languages;• have a strong understanding of regression and causal analysis; and• have experience applying machine learning and/or natural language processing to unstructured, messy data sets.

 

The ideal candidate for this position will have a passion for understanding K–12 American education through multiple types of data, have a general STEM background with a foundational understanding of data science, and be driven by open-minded, intellectual curiosity. Candidates who are able to participate in the program on an in-person basis for 30-40 hours a week are encouraged to apply.

 

About AEI Internships

 

AEI internships offer a unique opportunity for undergraduates, graduate students, and recent graduates to gain experience in research, writing, business, and communications at one of the nation’s leading think tanks. Competitive candidates will generally have a GPA of 3.5 or higher from a top-ranking college or university. AEI’s internship program runs for 12 weeks and all related programming will take place in Washington, DC. Please see the internship program home page for additional information about the program.

 

The start dates for the spring program are: January 13th and January 20th.

Overview

GIS Internship - Minneapolis, MN

Westwood Professional Services, Inc.

 

Westwood Professional Services, Inc. is seeking a GIS Intern to join our Renewables team. Westwood is a leading renewables, power, public infrastructure, and land development consulting firm dedicated to creating a better world for people though our work. Our core values – Relationships, Innovation, Dedication, Initiative, and Growth – are at the heart of everything we do. We believe in creating strong partnerships, fostering innovative solutions, committing passionately to our work, taking proactive steps towards progress, and nurturing personal and professional development.

 

The GIS Specialist Internship position will play a crucial role in our team, supporting our renewable energy projects with their technical expertise and innovative approaches to GIS. We are looking for a dynamic GIS Intern to enhance our team with their knowledge in spatial analysis, cartography, and data management. If you're passionate about GIS and ready to contribute to groundbreaking projects, we want to hear from you!

Duties and Responsibilities

  • Spatial Analysis & Cartography: Assist in creating, managing, analyzing, and displaying spatial data using GIS software.
  • Data Interpretation & Management: Learn to independently interpret data while maintaining comprehensive documentation. Assist in managing and updating existing GIS datasets, ensuring their relevance and accuracy.
  • Project Support: Contribute to the design and improvement of GIS methodologies for project efficiency. Support the project team by delivering tailored data and graphics solutions.
  • Technical Solutions: Help craft detailed and technically proficient solutions, presenting spatial data clearly and accurately across various media.
  • Collaborative Projects: Engage in diverse energy and land development projects, collaborating with cross-functional teams to provide GIS support and insights.
  • GIS Application Development: Assist in innovating desktop and mobile GIS applications, adhering to quality assurance and control standards.

You will be expected to:

    • Challenge current processes to develop new and more efficient processes.
    • Create tools and scripts to streamline frequently performed tasks.
    • Work with end users, create mapping products, and perform complex GIS analyses using the ArcGIS Platform.
    • Produce technically skilled and detailed solutions by preparing clear, complete, and accurate representations of spatial data using hardcopy and/or electronic media.
    • Develop and maintain geospatial data on desktop and mobile applications. Ensure data meets appropriate data accuracy and content standards for quality assurance and quality control.
    • You will work on energy projects, such as wind, solar, and transmission projects, land development, and public infrastructure projects.

Required Skills

  • Currently pursuing a degree in GIS, geography, or a related field with demonstrated capabilities in GIS.
  • Basic proficiency in ArcGIS software and geospatial analysis techniques.
  • Demonstrated ability to work with standard GIS datasets, deliverables, and software.
  • Understanding of different coordinate systems, map projections, and datums.
  • Basic understanding of standard cartographic methods, GIS principles, and spatial data management.
  • Capacity to manage multiple tasks independently and prioritize effectively.
  • Ability to solve complex problems related to GIS development and mapping.
  • Strong attention to detail and ability to work under pressure to meet deadlines.
  • Effective communication and collaboration skills.

Preferred Experience

  • Previous work in/familiarity with consulting engineers and/or surveyors is a plus.
  • Previous experience working on energy projects, such as transmission, solar, and wind, or land development projects.
  • Experience with remote sensing, GPS technology, and web mapping tools.
  • Experience using AutoCAD and DWG files.
  • Experience using Google Earth and KMZ files.
  • Familiarity with LiDAR datasets and usage.
  • Experience using Arcade expressions, Python, ModelBuilder, or another common GIS scripting language, as job duties may include creating scripts to streamline frequently performed tasks.
  • Experience as a consultant.
